WEBVTT

00:00.267 --> 00:01.934
I found her.

00:02.002 --> 00:03.802
Tamar Hodel.

00:03.870 --> 00:06.671
Right before you were born,
there was a trial.

00:06.673 --> 00:08.473
Fauna:
What kind of trial?

00:08.475 --> 00:09.808
With my father,
George Hodel.

00:09.876 --> 00:12.677
Improper acts,
improper relations.

00:12.746 --> 00:14.646
He made love to me.

00:17.017 --> 00:19.017
Is it true?

00:19.086 --> 00:21.019
He killed the Black Dahlia,
didn't he?

00:21.088 --> 00:22.154
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

00:22.222 --> 00:23.422
Elizabeth Short...

00:23.490 --> 00:25.424
Janice Brewster.

00:26.293 --> 00:27.359
We can stop him.

00:27.427 --> 00:28.893
[ Grunts ]
You can't.

00:28.895 --> 00:32.064
[ Gun clicks ]
The universe protects George.

00:34.101 --> 00:37.636
Jay: It was you, George.
It was you.

00:39.373 --> 00:42.240
[ Rachmaninoff's
"Etudes-Tableaux, Op. 39
No. 6" plays on piano ]

00:42.309 --> 00:51.916
♪♪

00:51.986 --> 00:54.620
♪♪

01:48.909 --> 01:53.778
But George's achievements
for a boy his age.

01:53.780 --> 01:55.914
His IQ is 186!

01:55.982 --> 01:57.982
Rachmaninoff:
Madam Hodel,

01:57.984 --> 02:00.185
I'm very sorry,
but I cannot teach him.

02:00.254 --> 02:01.654
Whyever not!

02:01.722 --> 02:03.722
His last instructor,
Dr. Simmeleman --

02:03.790 --> 02:05.323
Madam, please!

02:05.392 --> 02:06.791
Simmeleman?

02:06.861 --> 02:11.196
Your son, he is talented,
but he plays without emotion,

02:11.198 --> 02:13.398
the hardest thing
to have.

02:13.400 --> 02:14.533
It cannot be taught.

02:14.601 --> 02:16.068
At least I cannot teach it.

02:16.136 --> 02:18.671
He's a mimic,
a precise machine.

02:18.739 --> 02:20.873
Put him into medicine
or science.

02:20.941 --> 02:25.544
I beg your pardon,
Maestro Rachmaninoff.

02:25.612 --> 02:27.079
He is not an artist.

02:27.147 --> 02:29.548
Absurd!

02:29.616 --> 02:30.815
That's absurd!

02:30.817 --> 02:32.751
[ Door closes, thud ]

02:35.690 --> 02:37.622
[ Grunts ]

02:37.624 --> 02:43.228
♪♪

02:43.230 --> 02:48.267
♪♪

03:21.468 --> 03:22.835
[ Grunting ]

03:25.005 --> 03:26.538
[ Coughing ]

03:26.607 --> 03:28.607
[ Buzzer in distance ]

03:28.675 --> 03:29.742
You said medium rare,
right?

03:29.810 --> 03:33.278
-[ Groans ]
-Call it medium.

03:33.347 --> 03:35.014
[ Grunting ]

03:41.756 --> 03:43.087
You think
I like doing this?

03:43.089 --> 03:44.556
I hate this part of my job.

03:44.625 --> 03:46.158
Do you understand me?

03:46.226 --> 03:47.626
Now, I want you
to sit in there,

03:47.694 --> 03:49.628
and I want you to feel sorry
for yourself,

03:49.696 --> 03:50.963
and I want you
to be ashamed.

03:51.031 --> 03:53.365
Ain't one of you
supposed to be the good cop?

03:53.433 --> 03:55.634
-That was good cop.
-[ Groaning ]

03:57.504 --> 03:59.037
Wait!
Aah!

03:59.105 --> 04:00.305
[ Breathing heavily ]

04:01.508 --> 04:02.641
Wait.
Wait.

04:02.709 --> 04:04.042
[ Sniffs ]

04:04.110 --> 04:05.577
I know who killed
Janice Brewster.

04:05.646 --> 04:06.911
Janice Brewster?

04:06.913 --> 04:09.113
We had somebody
till your pal,

04:09.115 --> 04:11.316
the overeager
newspaper reporter,

04:11.318 --> 04:14.119
ran a story
and cleared Brody Stiles.

04:14.188 --> 04:15.587
George Hodel.

04:15.656 --> 04:17.790
You could someday
maybe walk out of here

04:17.858 --> 04:20.058
if you could just keep
that name off your lips.

04:20.126 --> 04:21.326
You're protecting
a killer.

04:21.395 --> 04:23.595
And you are dumber
than a box of rocks, man.

04:23.664 --> 04:24.997
What the hell does Hodel have,

04:25.065 --> 04:27.131
and why is he is so protected,
Billis, huh?!

04:27.133 --> 04:29.334
Hey, man, we just dot the I's
and cross the T's.

04:29.403 --> 04:32.471
No. Billis, I got --
I got proof! I got proof!

04:32.539 --> 04:34.939
It was on the table
when you walked into Ludong's.

04:34.941 --> 04:36.875
Billis!

04:36.943 --> 04:39.544
For once in your goddamn life,
be a cop!

04:39.546 --> 04:41.413
Billis: What did you say?
Be a cop instead
of a bag man for the mob!

04:41.482 --> 04:43.548
Is that why you joined
the force?
What did you say?

04:43.550 --> 04:45.484
Was that your dream
as a little boy?
Don't you ever say that to me!

04:45.552 --> 04:47.352
One blood test proves that
Tamar was telling the truth.
Give me the keys.

04:47.354 --> 04:48.687
That's why she's hiding
in Hawaii.

04:48.755 --> 04:49.954
He wanted that girl
I was with, too.

04:50.024 --> 04:51.023
What's the key?
Which is the key?

04:51.091 --> 04:52.357
Fauna. His granddaughter.
Why?

04:52.426 --> 04:54.092
Because he wanted to rape,
murder, and cut her up.

04:54.161 --> 04:56.829
She's 16 years old,
Billis!

04:56.897 --> 04:57.962
So what happens, huh?

04:58.032 --> 05:00.232
What happens
when it all falls apart?

05:00.300 --> 05:03.168
And Hodel falls apart,
and good old Billis

05:03.237 --> 05:06.371
is -- is left holding the bag
for a murderous pedophile

05:06.440 --> 05:08.973
that made a kid
with his own daughter!

05:09.043 --> 05:10.843
Huh? Is that why
you joined the force, huh?

05:10.911 --> 05:12.911
You don't talk about
why I joined the force!

05:12.979 --> 05:14.446
You understand me?
You understand me?

05:14.515 --> 05:16.915
You don't know what I deal with
on a day-to-day basis.

05:16.983 --> 05:19.784
I do. You're a cop.
You are a cop.

05:19.786 --> 05:21.920
So you do me a solid.

05:21.988 --> 05:25.590
And you look at Hodel,
and you look him in the eyes.

05:25.659 --> 05:28.327
[ Breathing heavily ]

05:30.531 --> 05:32.765
[ Breathing heavily ]

05:37.137 --> 05:40.272
[ Buzzer in distance ]

05:40.340 --> 05:43.075
[ Door clangs shut ]

05:43.143 --> 05:45.544
[ Telephone rings ]
Fauna: Hello?

05:45.612 --> 05:47.946
Sister Sarah: Hello.
I'm trying to reach Coretta Lee?

05:48.014 --> 05:49.748
She's not in.

05:49.816 --> 05:51.483
Please tell Coretta Lee
that her daughter,

05:51.552 --> 05:54.419
Jimmy Lee Faison, was admitted
to the ER last night.

05:54.421 --> 05:57.222
She's sedated and has been moved
to our intensive care unit.

05:57.224 --> 05:59.224
Jimmy Lee?
She's lost a lot of blood,

05:59.226 --> 06:02.827
and doctors are still working
to stabilize her.

06:02.897 --> 06:04.429
Please pass along
the message?

06:04.431 --> 06:06.765
We'll stay in touch with updates
on her status.

06:06.833 --> 06:08.934
[ Telephone ringing ]

06:11.772 --> 06:12.705
Hello?

06:12.773 --> 06:14.106
Fauna: Mrs. Huntington?

06:14.174 --> 06:15.708
Look, I need your help.

06:15.776 --> 06:18.277
[<i> Indistinct talking on radio</i> ]

06:24.851 --> 06:26.184
Terrence.

06:26.253 --> 06:28.987
Terrence,
where is everyone?

06:29.055 --> 06:31.123
Where the hell you been?
Has Xander come back?

06:31.191 --> 06:32.457
No.
Nobody's here.

06:32.459 --> 06:34.593
Shit.
They all out looking for Xander.

06:34.661 --> 06:36.595
We haven't seen him.
We don't know if he's in jail

06:36.663 --> 06:38.062
or laying in the streets
dead somewhere.

06:38.064 --> 06:39.798
The cops already killed
15 people.

06:39.866 --> 06:42.267
Jesus.

06:42.269 --> 06:45.003
They say that you took off
to Hawaii

06:45.071 --> 06:47.472
with some man,
some -- some white cat.

06:47.541 --> 06:48.607
Yeah, he's a reporter.

06:48.675 --> 06:50.542
He's -- He's trying to help me
find my mother.

06:50.611 --> 06:52.477
[ Helicopter blades whirring
in distance ]

06:52.479 --> 06:54.479
Terrence,
y-you gotta take me home.

06:54.548 --> 06:55.547
My mama, she's hurt.

06:55.616 --> 06:57.549
My car won't make it
to Nevada no how.

06:57.618 --> 06:59.684
Why don't you go back to Hawaii
w-with your white man?

06:59.686 --> 07:01.553
I gotta find Xander before
Big Momma have a heart attack.

07:01.622 --> 07:03.822
Can you take me
to Pasadena?
What?

07:03.890 --> 07:06.625
'Cause I can get cash, and then
I can take a bus from Pasadena,

07:06.693 --> 07:08.627
if you'll help me.

07:08.695 --> 07:11.496
They are yanking white folks
out of cars on Imperial,

07:11.498 --> 07:13.365
and shit,
the cops are worse.

07:13.434 --> 07:15.900
A black man driving a
light-skinned girl in Pasadena?

07:15.970 --> 07:17.302
I'll walk, then.

07:17.304 --> 07:19.805
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

07:21.508 --> 07:24.042
Wait!

07:24.111 --> 07:25.778
[ Indistinct shouting ]

07:25.846 --> 07:27.846
Man:<i> ...have been harassed</i>
<i> by brick-throwing Negroes</i>

07:27.914 --> 07:29.514
<i> as they attempt</i>
<i> to put out fires</i>

07:29.516 --> 07:31.383
<i> all along Imperial Highway.</i>

07:31.452 --> 07:32.985
<i>Rioting and looting can be seen</i>
<i> in liquor stores...</i>

07:33.053 --> 07:34.586
Man: Get your ass
off my street!

07:34.655 --> 07:36.188
[ Glass shatters ]
Get up out of here!

07:36.256 --> 07:37.389
Terrence: Hey, man!
This is my car, man!

07:37.458 --> 07:39.391
Get your ass off the street
right now!

07:39.460 --> 07:41.059
[ Siren wails ]
Wait, brother.
Look what you did to my car!

07:41.128 --> 07:43.128
Get on out of here,
Uncle Tom!

07:43.197 --> 07:44.729
[ Indistinct shouting ]

07:44.799 --> 07:48.266
<i> ...protect themselves</i>
<i> from snipers...</i>

07:48.335 --> 07:50.469
<i>Remain indoors and remain calm.</i>

07:50.537 --> 07:52.204
<i> Roadblocks</i>
<i> have been established</i>

07:52.272 --> 07:53.938
<i> around the perimeter</i>
<i> of the neighborhood.</i>

07:53.940 --> 07:55.407
[ Engine shuts off ]

07:55.476 --> 08:00.579
♪♪

08:01.482 --> 08:02.614
Man: Hey, boy!

08:02.683 --> 08:08.554
♪♪

08:18.298 --> 08:19.898
I wouldn't
park there today.

08:19.966 --> 08:22.167
You'll get a ticket.
It's Tuesday.

08:22.169 --> 08:23.335
[ Dog barks ]

08:25.506 --> 08:26.971
Yes, sir.

08:27.041 --> 08:28.306
♪♪

08:28.375 --> 08:30.442
[ Dog growls, barks ]

08:30.511 --> 08:34.013
♪♪

08:38.853 --> 08:40.118
[ Trunk opens ]

08:40.187 --> 08:45.657
♪♪

08:45.726 --> 08:46.591
[ Trunk closes ]

08:46.660 --> 08:47.860
Thank you.

08:47.928 --> 08:52.197
♪♪

08:52.199 --> 08:53.598
Go on home.
Be careful.

08:53.600 --> 08:56.601
What are you about to do?
Fauna!

08:56.603 --> 08:58.871
Where I'm going,
you can't come.

08:58.939 --> 09:00.272
Fauna!

09:00.340 --> 09:03.876
♪♪

09:10.685 --> 09:12.284
[ Lock clicks ]

09:12.353 --> 09:14.819
♪♪

09:14.889 --> 09:16.955
They've all gone mad.

09:17.023 --> 09:19.091
[ Door closes ]
They're burning down the city.

09:19.159 --> 09:20.759
It's terrifying!

09:20.827 --> 09:23.628
They'll be coming here next.
You know they will.

09:23.630 --> 09:25.430
God help us all.

09:25.499 --> 09:27.832
Man:<i> Hoodlums responding</i>
<i> to unfair arrests</i>

09:27.834 --> 09:30.102
<i> have taken to the streets</i>
<i> en masse,</i>

09:30.170 --> 09:31.836
<i> and rioting can be seen...</i>

09:31.906 --> 09:35.039
Mrs. Ho-- Huntington.

09:35.041 --> 09:36.708
I need your help.

09:36.777 --> 09:39.244
I'm sorry to ask,
but I need money for the bus.

09:39.246 --> 09:41.246
I need to get home.

09:41.248 --> 09:43.115
Oh, yes.

09:43.183 --> 09:45.517
Let me get you something
to drink first.

09:45.586 --> 09:47.452
You must be parched.

09:47.454 --> 09:50.189
[ Indistinct talking on TV ]

09:56.730 --> 09:58.297
Thank you.

10:09.276 --> 10:12.210
Mrs. Huntington.

10:12.279 --> 10:15.314
You should know,
I-I went to see Tamar.

10:18.819 --> 10:24.089
Is she still living
in her dream world?

10:25.626 --> 10:27.960
Well, yes.

10:28.028 --> 10:29.227
She believes it.

10:29.296 --> 10:31.896
That she hates me.

10:31.966 --> 10:34.099
I really
don't deserve that.

10:34.168 --> 10:37.202
No, um,
Tamar doesn't hate you.

10:38.973 --> 10:40.506
She forgives you.

10:46.580 --> 10:50.582
♪♪

10:50.651 --> 10:52.851
[ Glass clinks ]

10:52.919 --> 10:55.888
♪♪

11:02.062 --> 11:03.528
[ Glass thuds ]

11:03.597 --> 11:08.467
♪♪

11:13.874 --> 11:15.073
[ Grunts ]

11:15.142 --> 11:16.608
[ Thud ]

11:16.677 --> 11:19.011
♪♪

11:19.079 --> 11:21.145
[ Breathing heavily ]

11:21.147 --> 11:24.083
♪♪

11:31.692 --> 11:34.827
Don't eat anything
in his house.

11:34.895 --> 11:37.296
♪♪

11:52.712 --> 11:53.912
Officer Joe:
I'm telling you, Beans,

11:53.914 --> 11:55.313
you wouldn't believe it.
Move it along.

11:55.382 --> 11:56.648
Me and Bill pinned down
by sniper fire

11:56.716 --> 11:57.849
for 40 minutes...
That's it, that's it.

11:57.918 --> 11:59.384
...till we could even
get a cordon up.

11:59.453 --> 12:00.852
-Hands up!
-Walk away from one thing.

12:00.921 --> 12:01.987
-Don't sass me now.
-Six other things come up.

12:02.056 --> 12:03.388
-Yo. Hurry up.
-We're riding one way,

12:03.457 --> 12:04.590
-and the comes...
-Over there.

12:04.658 --> 12:05.457
..."Looting
on Imperial and Hoover."

12:05.525 --> 12:06.658
Cruisers going that way.

12:06.727 --> 12:08.794
We pass 'em,
lights and sirens.

12:08.862 --> 12:10.929
You know you ain't
getting backup

12:10.931 --> 12:13.131
'cause you can't
back anybody else up.

12:13.200 --> 12:14.666
Those fires, man,

12:14.735 --> 12:17.135
those firefighters
are getting shot at, man.

12:17.137 --> 12:18.336
What's gonna happen?

12:18.338 --> 12:21.072
That's it.
[ Door clangs shut ]

12:21.141 --> 12:23.342
[ Indistinct talking ]

12:26.280 --> 12:28.881
[ Doors clang shut ]

12:34.087 --> 12:37.355
What they got you
in here for, Al Capone?

12:37.425 --> 12:39.024
Look at you.

12:39.093 --> 12:40.692
Cell all to yourself.

12:40.761 --> 12:42.694
What's going on
out there?

12:42.762 --> 12:44.830
Hey, man,
we fighting back.

12:44.898 --> 12:47.433
Them damn cops beat up
on Marquette's mama,

12:47.501 --> 12:49.367
threw a pregnant woman
down on the ground.

12:49.437 --> 12:51.303
Folks is tired.

12:51.371 --> 12:54.506
Burning down
your own neighborhood.

12:54.574 --> 12:55.641
I can dig that.

12:55.709 --> 12:57.575
Man, we don't own
them damn businesses.

12:57.645 --> 12:59.777
We don't own shit.

12:59.779 --> 13:01.379
That's all them punk-ass
police care about

13:01.381 --> 13:03.381
is protecting them stores.

13:03.451 --> 13:05.250
They don't protect<i> us.</i>

13:05.319 --> 13:08.120
You live
in a different world.

13:08.188 --> 13:11.056
Think somebody will stand up
and right a wrong

13:11.125 --> 13:15.727
or stop an evil thing.

13:15.795 --> 13:17.729
It ain't like that
for us.

13:17.797 --> 13:20.265
If we don't put ourselves
on the line, then who will?

13:20.334 --> 13:27.539
♪♪

13:56.636 --> 13:58.470
Hodel:
How are you feeling?

14:00.240 --> 14:02.074
Come join me
in the sitting room.

14:04.912 --> 14:07.045
[ Door opens ]

14:07.047 --> 14:11.450
♪♪

14:21.461 --> 14:24.462
[<i> Slow piano music playing</i> ]

14:24.532 --> 14:29.501
♪♪

14:30.871 --> 14:33.671
Fauna:
How did I get here?

14:33.741 --> 14:35.874
Corinna called.

14:35.876 --> 14:38.944
You fainted
in her kitchen.

14:39.012 --> 14:40.412
I fainted?

14:40.480 --> 14:41.547
She was beside herself.

14:41.615 --> 14:44.082
Could barely speak,
poor thing.

14:44.084 --> 14:49.555
So, she called me, and I came
and brought you here.

14:49.623 --> 14:52.023
Not even the hospitals
are safe at the moment.

14:52.092 --> 14:55.594
♪♪

15:00.568 --> 15:02.034
How are you feeling?

15:02.102 --> 15:07.339
♪♪

15:15.583 --> 15:17.382
Healthy as a horse.

15:17.451 --> 15:23.055
♪♪

15:27.127 --> 15:29.327
George Hodel.

15:29.329 --> 15:33.531
I've been trying so hard
to get into contact with you.

15:33.533 --> 15:36.134
You invited me here.

15:36.136 --> 15:38.136
Do you remember?

15:38.205 --> 15:42.007
I am hard to pin down.

15:42.076 --> 15:44.209
Work, of course.

15:44.278 --> 15:46.812
My wife, Yuna,
has many talents,

15:46.880 --> 15:51.749
but the finer points of polish
seem to elude her.

15:51.751 --> 15:54.019
To be honest,
I find it relaxing.

15:54.087 --> 15:55.888
♪♪

16:00.428 --> 16:03.962
I met Tamar.

16:03.964 --> 16:05.831
And Jay Singletary.

16:09.236 --> 16:10.903
Oh, my goodness.

16:12.906 --> 16:15.441
You must think
I'm Lucifer himself.

16:15.509 --> 16:16.842
The two of them.

16:16.910 --> 16:19.311
What a trial for you.

16:19.379 --> 16:23.882
Well, I'm so sorry that<i> that</i>
was your introduction to me.

16:26.120 --> 16:30.722
You know, I'm not sure
what plagues Mr. Singletary.

16:30.791 --> 16:36.928
To begin with, he's a muckraker,
a yellow journalist.

16:36.997 --> 16:40.332
But whether it's due to
a brain imbalance of fluids

16:40.400 --> 16:44.269
or some war-time trauma,
he's a badly damaged man

16:44.338 --> 16:46.271
who's caused me
a tremendous amount of trouble

16:46.340 --> 16:47.873
over the years.

16:47.941 --> 16:51.010
You understand that I sued him
for libel and won?

16:53.280 --> 16:54.746
And what about Tamar?

16:54.815 --> 16:57.749
You found her in her hovel
on the beach?

16:57.818 --> 17:00.819
Surrounding
by squalling brats?

17:00.888 --> 17:03.088
I send her money,
of course.

17:03.157 --> 17:05.957
I wouldn't even say
Tamar is a liar, precisely,

17:06.026 --> 17:10.428
because she believes
her mis-truths so deeply.

17:10.430 --> 17:11.629
It's tragic.

17:11.699 --> 17:13.499
Shakespearean.

17:13.567 --> 17:16.702
Or at least
Eugene O'Neill.

17:19.840 --> 17:21.707
I'm gonna lay back down.

17:24.512 --> 17:26.644
Not feeling very well.

17:26.646 --> 17:32.384
♪♪

17:32.452 --> 17:33.285
♪♪

18:04.885 --> 18:06.752
[ Doorknob rattles ]

18:06.820 --> 18:09.821
♪♪

18:09.890 --> 18:11.557
[ Doorknob rattles ]

18:11.625 --> 18:18.296
♪♪

18:18.298 --> 18:24.636
♪♪

18:24.704 --> 18:26.572
[ Birds chirping ]

18:26.640 --> 18:28.506
[ Door rattles ]

18:28.508 --> 18:31.744
♪♪

18:43.524 --> 18:45.724
♪♪

18:45.792 --> 18:48.260
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

18:48.328 --> 18:52.731
♪♪

18:52.799 --> 18:55.534
Feeling better?

18:55.602 --> 18:56.935
Come and look.

19:01.942 --> 19:03.976
My latest acquisition.

19:05.212 --> 19:08.146
I'm very much
on the fence about it.

19:08.215 --> 19:11.416
I like it, I think.

19:11.418 --> 19:13.485
I can tell there's
something to it.

19:13.554 --> 19:17.956
But to be perfectly honest,
abstraction feels...

19:18.024 --> 19:19.958
faddish to me.

19:20.026 --> 19:22.026
Over-intellectual.

19:22.096 --> 19:24.229
What do you think?

19:24.231 --> 19:25.531
I wouldn't know.

19:28.235 --> 19:30.168
Like a window...

19:30.237 --> 19:35.507
we all peer through
from the outside.

19:35.576 --> 19:37.576
I imagine it feels familiar
to you,

19:37.644 --> 19:41.380
looking through windows
onto another world?

19:41.448 --> 19:43.648
What it must have been like
growing up

19:43.650 --> 19:47.586
among all those
simple people.

19:47.654 --> 19:48.853
Not belonging.

19:48.855 --> 19:50.188
[ Click ]

19:50.257 --> 19:53.859
There's so much happening
inside you.

19:56.397 --> 19:58.597
I think of myself
at your age.

19:58.665 --> 19:59.865
[ Lighter clicks ]

20:08.208 --> 20:10.875
You look well
in this house.

20:10.945 --> 20:13.145
It suits you.

20:13.213 --> 20:16.748
Would you stay
as my guest?

20:16.817 --> 20:20.619
My granddaughter?

20:20.687 --> 20:22.020
That's very kind.

20:22.088 --> 20:23.622
It is, isn't it?

20:23.690 --> 20:27.559
Well, I suppose you've
never had a proper home.

20:29.363 --> 20:31.964
Did you feel at home
with Jimmy Lee?

20:32.032 --> 20:33.966
[ Liquid pouring ]

20:37.304 --> 20:40.773
How is pretty Jimmy
these days?

20:40.841 --> 20:42.975
She's fine, I think.

20:43.043 --> 20:45.277
I haven't spoken to her
in a few weeks.

20:47.714 --> 20:48.847
Uh-huh.

20:48.915 --> 20:53.118
♪♪

20:53.187 --> 20:55.788
[ Doorbell ringing ]
Ah, yes.

20:55.856 --> 20:59.924
I have a meeting with
Mr. Berman from the clinic.

20:59.926 --> 21:01.660
You should go
to your room.

21:01.728 --> 21:05.063
Um, uh, I'd, uh --
I'd like to leave now.

21:05.132 --> 21:06.665
It's not safe, Fauna.

21:06.733 --> 21:09.802
Surely you can see that.

21:09.870 --> 21:11.670
Dr. Hodel.

21:11.738 --> 21:15.674
Terribly sorry
to disturb you, sir.

21:15.742 --> 21:18.076
Fauna, go.

21:18.144 --> 21:22.681
♪♪

21:22.749 --> 21:25.750
Hodel: Sergeant Billis,
not at all expecting to see you.

21:25.820 --> 21:28.086
You fellows have certainly
got the tiger by the tail,

21:28.155 --> 21:30.089
haven't you?

21:31.558 --> 21:34.493
Are armed Negroes,
wearing red armbands,

21:34.561 --> 21:36.028
invading
white neighborhoods?

21:36.096 --> 21:37.095
[ Liquid pours ]

21:37.164 --> 21:38.497
Communists?

21:38.565 --> 21:40.432
Hard to tell
these days, sir.

21:40.501 --> 21:42.300
We got that reporter
wrapped up.

21:42.369 --> 21:44.569
Just thought
you should know.

21:44.638 --> 21:47.372
I've spoken to
the Lieutenant Governor.

21:47.441 --> 21:49.842
You know, of course,
the National Guard
is being deployed.

21:49.910 --> 21:51.776
I did not know that, sir.
[ Doorbell ringing ]

21:51.778 --> 21:54.246
I'm having them send a squad
here to the house.

21:54.314 --> 21:56.581
Soldiers are
what I need now.

21:56.650 --> 21:58.050
Not police.

21:59.920 --> 22:01.720
Yuna: Dr. Hodel?

22:01.788 --> 22:03.922
It's Mr. Berman.

22:03.990 --> 22:06.124
Show yourself out,
Billis.

22:06.193 --> 22:09.161
♪♪

22:19.273 --> 22:21.673
Are you
a police officer?

22:21.742 --> 22:23.876
Who are you?

22:23.944 --> 22:25.544
C-Could you take me
with you?

22:25.612 --> 22:27.212
Out of this house,
please.

22:27.281 --> 22:28.881
[ Footsteps approaching ]

22:28.949 --> 22:30.349
Hodel: Fauna?

22:32.887 --> 22:36.020
No.
Better not.

22:36.090 --> 22:37.622
You should be
in your room.

22:37.691 --> 22:40.426
♪♪

23:12.727 --> 23:15.260
[ Buzzer ]

23:15.262 --> 23:16.929
[ Clang ]

23:16.997 --> 23:19.664
Wake up.
Billis wants to talk.

23:19.733 --> 23:20.799
[ Keys jingling ]

23:20.867 --> 23:22.066
[ Indistinct talking
in distance ]

23:22.068 --> 23:24.336
[ Door opens ]

23:24.404 --> 23:26.605
[ Door buzzes ]

23:30.144 --> 23:31.410
[ Door closes ]

23:33.547 --> 23:35.080
You guys
don't look so good.

23:35.149 --> 23:38.150
You neither, beaver.
You wouldn't like it out there.

23:38.218 --> 23:39.818
I might.

23:39.886 --> 23:41.286
Cuddy, make sure
he's listening.

23:41.288 --> 23:42.821
No, no, no.
I'm listening.

23:42.889 --> 23:44.823
[ Coughs ]

23:44.891 --> 23:46.224
Paying attention?

23:46.293 --> 23:47.960
Say it.
Say it.

23:48.028 --> 23:51.096
[ Inhales sharply ]

23:51.165 --> 23:53.232
[ Grunting ]
Paying attention.

23:55.235 --> 23:58.436
So, I looked
at all your evidence.

23:58.505 --> 24:01.173
Got the pictures developed.
[ Coughs ]

24:01.241 --> 24:03.908
Not much there, pal.

24:03.978 --> 24:04.977
What else you got?

24:05.045 --> 24:06.444
Let me out, Billis.

24:06.513 --> 24:09.514
For Christ's sake.

24:09.516 --> 24:11.450
We'll bury Hodel
under a mountain of shit.

24:11.518 --> 24:12.985
You'll be
the hero detective.

24:13.053 --> 24:15.720
Don't you want that?

24:15.790 --> 24:19.191
Well, can't do that.

24:19.259 --> 24:21.660
There's too many problems.

24:21.728 --> 24:23.061
You got
credibility issues.

24:23.130 --> 24:25.464
Even if I was, which I'm not,
it wouldn't be with you.

24:25.532 --> 24:28.000
Nothing you have
would hold up.

24:28.068 --> 24:30.402
So, what else do you have?

24:30.471 --> 24:31.804
Because I'm gonna
need solid gold.

24:31.872 --> 24:33.405
Did you -- Did you see him?
Did you go see him?

24:33.474 --> 24:34.739
Yeah, I went to the house.
The girl's there.

24:34.809 --> 24:36.074
The granddaughter's there
in the house.

24:36.142 --> 24:37.275
She is?

24:37.344 --> 24:38.943
Are you gonna do anything
about it?

24:38.945 --> 24:41.480
You better watch
what you say right now.

24:41.548 --> 24:42.815
I'd be very, very careful
if I were you,

24:42.883 --> 24:44.349
'cause I'd have
Cuddy cut your throat,

24:44.418 --> 24:45.818
throw you in the cell,
call it solved.

24:45.886 --> 24:47.219
Is that the plan?

24:47.287 --> 24:49.021
Oh, God damn it.

24:49.089 --> 24:50.555
Billis, you saw the photos,
right?

24:50.557 --> 24:52.290
You saw it.
You know I'm not crazy.

24:52.359 --> 24:54.693
-You saw it.
-I saw it.

24:54.761 --> 24:57.162
And what -- what, that's all?
You know he's the guy.

24:57.164 --> 25:00.032
You know what's gonna happen,
what's maybe already happened.

25:00.100 --> 25:02.567
So do something!
Look at me.

25:02.569 --> 25:04.369
This is very important
that you listen to me.

25:04.438 --> 25:06.371
I'll put this cigarette out
in your eye.

25:06.440 --> 25:08.707
Look at me!

25:08.775 --> 25:12.511
First of all, neither you
nor God tells me what to do.

25:12.579 --> 25:17.516
Second...
<i> maybe</i> we'll handle it.

25:17.584 --> 25:19.384
But a decision like that
takes months.

25:19.453 --> 25:21.453
Hodel's got too many
by the big balls,

25:21.522 --> 25:23.655
and it's not just
our top brass protecting him.

25:23.724 --> 25:25.390
It's DeSimone.
It's the Licata family.

25:25.459 --> 25:26.525
It's everybody.

25:26.593 --> 25:28.060
I do something like that
on my own,

25:28.128 --> 25:30.462
I'm dead in a week.

25:30.531 --> 25:33.365
[ Scoffs ]
Have a good day, pal.

25:35.202 --> 25:36.735
Wait, wait.

25:36.803 --> 25:38.403
Hey, hey, hey.
Wait a minute.

25:38.472 --> 25:41.140
♪♪

25:46.413 --> 25:47.612
I got something.

25:47.681 --> 25:49.848
-No, you don't.
-Yeah, I do.

25:51.818 --> 25:54.419
That knife --
That knife right there.

25:54.488 --> 25:56.621
That's my
second-favorite knife.

25:56.690 --> 25:59.424
That's the knife that killed
Janice Brewster.

25:59.493 --> 26:00.893
You get the M.E.
to testify to that,

26:00.961 --> 26:03.362
the D.A.
will go along with it, huh?

26:03.430 --> 26:04.829
Cuddy's
second-favorite knife.

26:04.899 --> 26:06.431
You put my fingerprints
all over that,

26:06.500 --> 26:08.833
I'll sign a full confession
for Janice Brewster.

26:08.903 --> 26:10.703
-What game are you playing?
-You cut me loose.

26:10.771 --> 26:13.171
The city's going crazy.
I get lost in the shuffle.

26:13.240 --> 26:16.241
Lose me for a couple hours,
and I will kill Hodel,

26:16.243 --> 26:17.376
and you know I'll do it.

26:17.444 --> 26:18.777
That's your solution,
Billis.

26:18.845 --> 26:20.512
Two problems gone.
All your problems gone.

26:20.581 --> 26:22.447
You're a genius.

26:22.516 --> 26:29.387
♪♪

26:29.456 --> 26:32.056
I get a full confession?

26:32.058 --> 26:33.858
Prints on the knife?

26:33.860 --> 26:35.527
What'll you do,
I don't cut you loose?

26:35.596 --> 26:37.395
Aren't you sick and tired
of wiping his ass?

26:37.464 --> 26:39.464
Aren't you sick
of looking at my face?

26:39.533 --> 26:41.867
You kill two birds
with one stone.

26:43.070 --> 26:44.869
It's elegant.

26:44.871 --> 26:49.641
♪♪

27:30.384 --> 27:31.115
[ Chuckles ]

27:31.117 --> 27:34.586
♪♪

27:34.655 --> 27:36.822
I was supposed to
be a journalist.

27:47.934 --> 27:49.934
Yeah, well...
[ Door buzzes ]

27:49.936 --> 27:52.136
...I don't think
that's gonna work out.

27:52.138 --> 27:57.209
♪♪

27:57.277 --> 27:58.911
[ Door closes ]

28:06.286 --> 28:07.886
[ Engine starts ]

28:07.954 --> 28:09.354
[ Siren wails in distance ]

28:09.356 --> 28:10.422
[ Indistinct talking ]

28:10.491 --> 28:12.057
[ Whistles ]

28:14.028 --> 28:15.694
Dickhead.

28:15.762 --> 28:18.030
Why do I feel like I'm gonna
get shot in the back

28:18.098 --> 28:19.164
trying to escape?

28:19.233 --> 28:22.100
'Cause you have no faith
in our institutions.

28:22.169 --> 28:24.969
Just do me a favor.
Try not to kill Jim, okay?

28:25.039 --> 28:26.171
What?

28:26.173 --> 28:27.639
His uncles
are all captains.

28:27.708 --> 28:30.242
Guy's a real prick,
but please, promise me

28:30.310 --> 28:31.977
that you will not kill him.

28:33.313 --> 28:35.514
[ Car door opens ]

28:35.582 --> 28:37.716
Hey, Jimmy.
Thanks.

28:37.784 --> 28:39.518
[ Police radio chatter ]

28:39.586 --> 28:40.652
Jim: Screw you, Billis.

28:40.721 --> 28:41.854
Billis: Wow.

28:44.658 --> 28:46.859
Hey, Jimmy! Hold up!
Where you headed?

28:46.927 --> 28:48.326
Hollywood.
Transfer.

28:48.395 --> 28:50.595
Great. Our cars are up there.
Give us a ride, huh?

28:50.664 --> 28:52.164
Yeah, yeah.
Jump in.

28:53.267 --> 28:54.533
[ Car door closes ]

28:54.601 --> 28:59.538
♪♪

28:59.606 --> 29:02.207
[ Car doors close ]

29:02.276 --> 29:05.410
[ Police radio chatter ]

29:05.412 --> 29:07.446
[ Engine starts ]

29:49.256 --> 29:50.823
[ Lock clicks ]

29:54.661 --> 29:56.795
Dinner is served.

29:58.065 --> 30:01.065
[<i> Classical music playing</i> ]

30:01.067 --> 30:04.770
♪♪

30:26.493 --> 30:27.893
Good night, Yuna.

30:48.783 --> 30:52.250
Aren't you hungry?

30:52.319 --> 30:54.787
Not right now.

30:54.855 --> 30:57.923
I'm just not feeling well.

30:59.460 --> 31:01.627
[ Chuckles ]

31:04.198 --> 31:06.999
[ Fork clatters ]

31:07.067 --> 31:08.267
Well...

31:10.471 --> 31:13.138
To your
very fine health.

31:27.621 --> 31:29.455
[ Slurps ]

32:06.793 --> 32:09.594
Did you know
I'm a painter?

32:09.596 --> 32:13.265
Well, I dabble, anyway.

32:13.333 --> 32:14.466
Sit for me.

32:14.535 --> 32:15.868
-I'll paint you.
-What?

32:15.936 --> 32:18.270
If we're not going to eat,
we should work, create,

32:18.338 --> 32:19.538
chase our own divinity.

32:19.606 --> 32:20.606
Here?

32:32.086 --> 32:33.418
Nasty thing.

32:33.420 --> 32:36.555
Still, better safe than sorry
on a night like tonight.

32:41.762 --> 32:43.028
This way.

33:04.785 --> 33:06.785
[ Door closes, lock clicks ]

33:06.853 --> 33:14.193
♪♪

33:28.875 --> 33:32.244
I'm very safe
and secure here.

33:34.281 --> 33:39.551
Of course, oil portraiture
isn't my forte.

33:39.620 --> 33:42.687
My focus lies elsewhere.

33:42.689 --> 33:47.826
But I do find it an essential
step, so please, bear with me.

33:47.894 --> 33:48.861
Oh.

33:55.035 --> 33:58.236
You'll need
to wear this.

33:58.305 --> 33:59.304
Just this.

34:01.776 --> 34:04.643
You can change
behind the curtain.

34:04.711 --> 34:06.211
I don't want to.

34:07.848 --> 34:09.247
[ Gasps ]

34:09.316 --> 34:10.449
[ Thud ]

34:10.517 --> 34:13.452
[ Breathes shakily ]

34:13.520 --> 34:15.754
Let's not have any more of that,
shall we?

34:21.195 --> 34:22.194
Change.

34:32.807 --> 34:34.873
[ Breathing heavily ]

34:34.941 --> 34:38.577
♪♪

34:47.488 --> 34:49.754
Is it true?

34:49.756 --> 34:51.824
What Jay said?

34:51.892 --> 34:54.226
Who, the reporter?

34:54.294 --> 34:57.095
Oh, it's Jay now,
is it?

34:57.164 --> 34:59.231
My, aren't we chummy?

34:59.299 --> 35:02.767
Jay wouldn't know a single
true thing about me.

35:02.769 --> 35:07.039
You can't compare me to normal,
ordinary men

35:07.107 --> 35:08.973
or expect me
to follow their laws.

35:08.975 --> 35:10.476
[ Cigarette case clicks ]

35:13.180 --> 35:16.448
The surrealists in the end
were cowards.

35:16.517 --> 35:20.385
They lacked the moral strength
to see their philosophy through.

35:20.387 --> 35:24.989
They made pictures of what
they dreamed and desired.

35:25.059 --> 35:26.991
[ Clink ]
How quaint.

35:27.061 --> 35:29.461
[ Lighter clicks ]

35:29.530 --> 35:34.833
I've traveled as far from them
as a star from a worm.

35:42.677 --> 35:44.743
The Marquis de Sade wrote,

35:44.811 --> 35:49.081
"I have no need to thwart
my inclinations

35:49.149 --> 35:52.084
in order to flatter
some God.

35:52.152 --> 35:54.887
These instincts were given
to me by nature,

35:54.955 --> 35:58.690
and it would irritate her
were I to resist them.

35:58.759 --> 36:00.693
If she gave me bad ones,

36:00.761 --> 36:05.029
that is because they were
necessary to her designs.

36:05.031 --> 36:07.766
I am in her hands...

36:07.834 --> 36:10.168
but a machine...

36:10.237 --> 36:13.705
which runs as she likes."

36:13.774 --> 36:15.307
Sit.

36:15.376 --> 36:21.613
♪♪

36:32.225 --> 36:35.260
[ Sirens wailing in distance ]

36:36.163 --> 36:38.597
[ Police radio chatter ]

36:50.711 --> 36:52.645
[ Clicking ]

37:02.923 --> 37:04.456
Jim: Hey, jackass!

37:04.525 --> 37:06.792
There's a curfew,
and you're in violation!

37:06.860 --> 37:08.727
Go home!

37:08.796 --> 37:12.463
Man, some people are just
too stupid to live.

37:12.465 --> 37:14.599
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, too stupid.

37:14.668 --> 37:15.867
[ Laughter ]

37:15.869 --> 37:17.736
These idiots smoking dope
and skipping rope

37:17.805 --> 37:19.738
all the way down here
from Avalon.
[ Handcuffs click ]

37:19.807 --> 37:23.142
[ Laughter ]

37:23.210 --> 37:24.876
[ Grunts ]

37:24.945 --> 37:26.745
-Aah!
-Ohh!

37:26.814 --> 37:28.547
[ Tires screeching ]

37:33.286 --> 37:35.087
[ Gunshots ]

37:38.025 --> 37:40.059
[ Horn blaring ]

37:48.569 --> 37:50.602
[ Grunting ]

37:55.042 --> 37:56.542
[ Blaring stops ]

37:57.578 --> 37:59.044
[ Grunts ]

37:59.112 --> 38:00.846
[ Breathing heavily ]

38:02.115 --> 38:04.115
[ Fire crackling ]

38:04.185 --> 38:08.687
♪♪

38:15.729 --> 38:17.863
[ Sobbing ]
I need to wipe my face.

38:24.271 --> 38:26.572
[ Sobbing ]

38:29.476 --> 38:31.610
Please, please,
don't hurt me.

38:31.679 --> 38:34.279
Hodel:
This is your special moment.

38:34.347 --> 38:36.882
Let's not spoil it
with hysterics.

38:38.685 --> 38:39.885
Just yet.

38:39.953 --> 38:42.020
♪♪

38:42.089 --> 38:43.589
[ Sobbing ]

38:47.961 --> 38:52.564
Get up, silly,
or something bad could happen.

38:52.566 --> 38:55.366
[ Gun clicks ]

38:55.368 --> 38:57.236
Fauna!

38:57.304 --> 38:59.104
Don't be a goose.

38:59.172 --> 39:00.806
Get back in your place.

39:15.388 --> 39:18.257
Keep your face up.

39:18.325 --> 39:23.262
Your dreams are more real,
more true than your reality.

39:23.330 --> 39:24.729
But you must remove the veil

39:24.798 --> 39:27.933
society places over all of us
after childhood.

39:31.538 --> 39:33.305
You sure
talk a lot of shit.

39:40.414 --> 39:43.749
I went to Corinna Huntington's
Happening.

39:43.817 --> 39:46.017
I know what Corinna
would call this.

39:46.087 --> 39:49.154
She'd say it was the opposite
of avant-garde.

39:49.222 --> 39:52.824
She'd say "kitsch."

39:52.893 --> 39:55.094
No one speaks to me
like that.

39:55.162 --> 39:58.830
Corinna said "literalism means
you're simple-minded."

39:58.899 --> 40:01.166
What does that say
about you?

40:01.234 --> 40:03.702
Corinna's the real artist.
Ain't that something?

40:03.771 --> 40:08.440
She's the one whose name they're
gonna remember in 100 years.

40:08.509 --> 40:11.110
You're nothing.

40:11.178 --> 40:15.046
Another daughter of mine
that no one will believe.

40:15.116 --> 40:17.916
The artists, the ones
you call cowards,

40:17.985 --> 40:20.786
they were talking
in symbols, dummy.

40:20.854 --> 40:24.189
Jimmy Lee said she didn't need
to understand a song to sing it.

40:24.257 --> 40:25.657
But that ain't true, is it?

40:25.659 --> 40:28.527
You're just like her, making art
without understanding.

40:28.595 --> 40:30.595
Even what you were just saying,
nature made you a machine?

40:30.664 --> 40:32.798
What a bunch of shit.

40:32.866 --> 40:34.666
I'd rather not start
so soon.

40:34.735 --> 40:35.600
Aah!

40:35.669 --> 40:37.202
[ Screams ]
Aah!

40:37.270 --> 40:39.538
I'll show you pain,
bigger than anything --

40:39.606 --> 40:40.906
-Aah!
-[ Grunts ]

40:54.888 --> 40:56.488
How dare you.

40:57.958 --> 41:00.692
Aah! Damn it!

41:00.761 --> 41:04.430
You -- You can't
get away.

41:05.966 --> 41:10.101
Whatever you are,
you're mine, most of all.

41:10.171 --> 41:13.505
Mine more than anything.

41:13.574 --> 41:17.042
Am I your daughter?

41:17.110 --> 41:18.344
George?

41:22.983 --> 41:26.117
[ Gun cocks ]

41:26.119 --> 41:28.020
[ Breathing heavily ]

41:31.658 --> 41:33.826
[ Bull growling ]

41:40.067 --> 41:41.800
No.

41:41.869 --> 41:44.203
Not yours.

41:44.271 --> 41:47.072
I know who I am.

41:47.140 --> 41:52.011
I'm Jimmy Lee's daughter.
I will never be yours.

41:52.079 --> 41:55.146
We all know what you are,
George.

41:55.216 --> 41:57.148
You're a cliché.

41:57.150 --> 41:59.852
Just like a pimp,
raping his own daughter.

42:20.574 --> 42:23.575
It's boring, George.

42:23.644 --> 42:28.847
Pretending simple urges
are high art.

42:28.916 --> 42:30.416
You're boring.

42:42.729 --> 42:44.630
[ Light switch clicks ]

42:48.935 --> 42:52.504
♪♪

42:52.573 --> 42:54.106
Fauna: Jay?

43:05.452 --> 43:06.819
[ Shoes clatter ]

43:10.657 --> 43:11.656
[ Gun clatters ]

43:11.725 --> 43:13.092
[ Sobs ]

43:20.200 --> 43:23.268
Are you okay?

43:23.270 --> 43:24.403
I'm all right.

43:35.682 --> 43:37.616
You stay here.

43:40.554 --> 43:41.854
Jay.

43:52.633 --> 43:54.233
[ Light switch clicks ]

44:13.520 --> 44:15.988
[ Breathing heavily ]

44:20.927 --> 44:23.595
[<i> Bull roars</i> ]

44:25.466 --> 44:26.531
[ Clattering ]

44:26.533 --> 44:28.533
Jay: You son of a bitch!

44:28.602 --> 44:32.136
[ Shouting ]

44:32.138 --> 44:32.871
Fauna: Jay!

44:32.939 --> 44:35.140
[ Shouting ]

44:35.142 --> 44:36.675
Jay, stop!

44:36.743 --> 44:39.411
Aah!
You don't get to walk!

44:39.480 --> 44:40.879
[ Glass shatters ]

44:40.947 --> 44:42.547
He's gone, Jay.

44:42.616 --> 44:45.017
Jay. Jay, listen to me.
I have to get him.
I have to get him.

44:45.085 --> 44:46.951
-Listen to me, Jay!
-Where are you?!

44:46.953 --> 44:48.220
Jay, Jay, Jay!

44:48.288 --> 44:51.156
-Jay, look at me.
-I will die to find him.

44:51.158 --> 44:52.424
-Jay.
-I'll die to get him.

44:52.493 --> 44:53.558
-Jay!
-I'll die to get him!

44:53.627 --> 44:56.161
Look at me.
Look at me.

44:57.431 --> 44:59.164
Look at me.
Look at me.

44:59.233 --> 45:00.966
[ Breathing heavily ]

45:03.370 --> 45:06.771
You don't have to.

45:06.773 --> 45:07.906
Okay.

45:10.645 --> 45:12.411
Let's go.

45:18.785 --> 45:20.653
[ Sirens wailing in distance ]

45:20.721 --> 45:24.923
♪♪

45:26.460 --> 45:28.060
I don't want to tell
your story anymore.

45:28.128 --> 45:31.063
I just want you
to get away.

45:31.131 --> 45:34.667
Just walk away
and never come back.

45:34.735 --> 45:37.802
You can tell it.
I don't mind.

45:37.872 --> 45:39.738
I won't.

45:42.008 --> 45:45.744
I think there's grace for you,
Jay, if you can find it.

45:49.216 --> 45:50.182
Is there?

46:04.831 --> 46:07.700
I gotta leave town.

46:07.768 --> 46:11.369
Send me a postcard.

46:11.438 --> 46:13.072
I'll write you.

46:16.443 --> 46:17.343
Sure.

47:13.567 --> 47:16.701
[ Indistinct talking on PA ]

47:16.703 --> 47:22.707
♪♪

47:22.709 --> 47:22.841
♪♪

47:28.382 --> 47:30.816
You gonna bring your man
up in here?

47:34.054 --> 47:36.388
You know I ain't done my hair
in two weeks.

47:38.325 --> 47:40.526
You're still
Pretty Jimmy, Mama.

47:55.742 --> 47:58.677
Fauna:<i> "Dear Jay...</i>

47:58.745 --> 48:02.014
<i> I hope this finds you.</i>

48:02.082 --> 48:04.817
<i> I hope you found a life</i>
<i> somewhere down there.</i>

48:13.694 --> 48:15.494
<i> Things here have changed.</i>

48:17.297 --> 48:18.963
<i> Feels like</i>
<i> the more they change,</i>

48:18.965 --> 48:20.799
<i> the more they stay the same.</i>

48:23.237 --> 48:27.639
<i> I feel lost</i>
<i> and alone sometimes.</i>

48:27.708 --> 48:31.844
<i> Feel so different</i>
<i> than everyone around me.</i>

48:31.912 --> 48:35.247
<i> Like you feel.</i>

48:35.315 --> 48:38.150
<i> Maybe it's because we know</i>
<i> what monsters are.</i>

48:41.988 --> 48:43.822
<i> We know what makes 'em.</i>

48:47.061 --> 48:49.327
<i> And I know what unmakes 'em.</i>

48:49.396 --> 48:55.134
♪♪

49:03.143 --> 49:06.211
<i> We keep struggling, making do,</i>
<i> and going on,</i>

49:06.280 --> 49:08.213
<i> 'cause that's all there is.</i>

49:18.625 --> 49:21.560
<i> When you look in the mirror,</i>
<i> Jay,</i>

49:21.628 --> 49:23.562
<i> I hope you can live</i>
<i> with what you see.</i>

49:29.570 --> 49:32.504
<i> The devil is something</i>
<i> we all carry in our hearts.</i>

49:34.641 --> 49:37.042
<i> We have to make peace</i>
<i> with him, Jay.</i>

49:41.382 --> 49:43.382
<i> We have to find another way.</i>

49:47.387 --> 49:53.125
<i> What you did and didn't do,</i>
<i> that saved me.</i>

49:53.193 --> 49:58.397
<i> You may not believe it,</i>
<i> but it saved me.</i>

49:58.465 --> 50:00.799
<i> People around me</i>
<i> are a sunny day,</i>

50:00.867 --> 50:05.003
<i> living their lives wide open</i>
<i> without secrets.</i>

50:05.071 --> 50:11.676
<i> When I look in the mirror,</i>
<i> Jay, I see something else.</i>

50:11.678 --> 50:14.146
<i> Something I don't</i>
<i> quite recognize.</i>

50:17.083 --> 50:18.883
<i> But something I chose."</i>

50:18.885 --> 50:24.456
♪♪

50:49.850 --> 50:54.153
